{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/blog/attrition/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Developer's blog"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"2f83c5f4-0dc0-515c-9917-abb076bc56ec","excerpt":"Meaning Attrition is a noun that means a gradual reduction in the number, strength, or effectiveness of something, especially through natural or continuous loss…","tableOfContents":"<ul>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#meaning\">Meaning</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#grammar-and-usage\">Grammar and Usage</a></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#types-of-attrition-business-context\">Types of Attrition (Business Context)</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#common-phrases\">Common Phrases</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#collocations\">Collocations</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#examples\">Examples</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#synonyms-or-related\">Synonyms or Related</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#antonym\">Antonym</a></p>\n</li>\n</ul>","html":"<h2 id=\"meaning\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#meaning\" aria-label=\"meaning permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Meaning</h2>\n<p><strong>Attrition</strong> is a noun that means a gradual reduction in the number, strength, or effectiveness of something, especially through <strong>natural or continuous loss</strong> (such as employees leaving a company, customers declining, or resources wearing away).</p>\n<p>In business, “attrition” often refers to <strong>employee turnover</strong> — the rate at which employees leave a company and are not immediately replaced.</p>\n<h2 id=\"grammar-and-usage\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#grammar-and-usage\" aria-label=\"grammar and usage permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Grammar and Usage</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Part of speech:</strong> Noun</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Uncountable noun</strong> (usually used without “a”)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Common structures:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>employee attrition rate</em></li>\n<li><em>attrition through natural causes</em></li>\n<li><em>reduce attrition by improving job satisfaction</em></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"types-of-attrition-business-context\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#types-of-attrition-business-context\" aria-label=\"types of attrition business context permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Types of Attrition (Business Context)</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Voluntary attrition</strong>: Employees choose to leave.</li>\n<li><strong>Involuntary attrition</strong>: Employees are terminated or laid off.</li>\n<li><strong>Natural attrition</strong>: Positions are left unfilled after departures.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"common-phrases\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#common-phrases\" aria-label=\"common phrases permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Common Phrases</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>employee attrition</strong></li>\n<li><strong>customer attrition</strong></li>\n<li><strong>attrition rate</strong></li>\n<li><strong>natural attrition</strong></li>\n<li><strong>reduce attrition</strong></li>\n<li><strong>attrition level</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"collocations\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#collocations\" aria-label=\"collocations permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Collocations</h2>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Verb + attrition</th>\n<th>Noun + attrition</th>\n<th>Adjective + attrition</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>reduce attrition</td>\n<td>employee attrition</td>\n<td>natural attrition</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>measure attrition</td>\n<td>customer attrition</td>\n<td>high attrition</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>manage attrition</td>\n<td>staff attrition</td>\n<td>low attrition</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>calculate attrition</td>\n<td>workforce attrition</td>\n<td>gradual attrition</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h2 id=\"examples\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#examples\" aria-label=\"examples permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Examples</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>The company is facing a high <strong>employee attrition rate</strong> due to poor management.</li>\n<li>HR implemented new policies to <strong>reduce attrition</strong> and improve morale.</li>\n<li><strong>Customer attrition</strong> has increased since the competitor launched a similar product.</li>\n<li>The <strong>attrition of troops</strong> during the long battle weakened the army.</li>\n<li>Over time, <strong>natural attrition</strong> reduced the workforce by 10%.</li>\n<li>Colleges often experience some level of <strong>student attrition</strong> each semester.</li>\n<li>The manager analyzed the <strong>attrition data</strong> to identify retention problems.</li>\n<li>In marketing, <strong>customer attrition</strong> is also called “churn.”</li>\n<li>The company plans to cut costs through <strong>attrition rather than layoffs</strong>.</li>\n<li>The <strong>attrition of materials</strong> in the machine led to frequent repairs.</li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"synonyms-or-related\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#synonyms-or-related\" aria-label=\"synonyms or related permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Synonyms or Related</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>turnover</li>\n<li>reduction</li>\n<li>erosion</li>\n<li>decline</li>\n<li>weakening</li>\n<li>loss</li>\n<li>decay</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"antonym\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#antonym\" aria-label=\"antonym permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Antonym</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>retention</li>\n<li>growth</li>\n<li>recruitment</li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"title":"attrition meaning and examples","date":"2025-10-30","description":"English learning materials; attrition explanation.","tags":["English","noun","business","HR"],"featuredImage":{"publicURL":"/static/9c1f8fdbd88d770ce63bbeffc11ecc9f/attrition.png","childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","backgroundColor":"#f8e8c8","images":{"fallback":{"src":"/static/9c1f8fdbd88d770ce63bbeffc11ecc9f/b5658/attrition.png","srcSet":"/static/9c1f8fdbd88d770ce63bbeffc11ecc9f/acb7c/attrition.png 256w,\n/static/9c1f8fdbd88d770ce63bbeffc11ecc9f/ccc41/attrition.png 512w,\n/static/9c1f8fdbd88d770ce63bbeffc11ecc9f/b5658/attrition.png 1024w","sizes":"(min-width: 1024px) 1024px, 100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/static/9c1f8fdbd88d770ce63bbeffc11ecc9f/22bfc/attrition.webp 256w,\n/static/9c1f8fdbd88d770ce63bbeffc11ecc9f/d689f/attrition.webp 512w,\n/static/9c1f8fdbd88d770ce63bbeffc11ecc9f/67ded/attrition.webp 1024w","type":"image/webp","sizes":"(min-width: 1024px) 1024px, 100vw"}]},"width":1024,"height":1024}}}}},"relatedPosts":{"nodes":[]},"previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/discrepancy/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"discrepancy meaning and examples"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/enhance/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"enhance meaning and examples"}}},"pageContext":{"id":"2f83c5f4-0dc0-515c-9917-abb076bc56ec","previousPostId":"41ab33de-a816-5793-b6f9-91c36b0b0f3b","nextPostId":"c650799f-49a0-53b5-9c34-fd8353b9641b","relatedPosts":[]}},"staticQueryHashes":["2841359383"],"slicesMap":{}}